This function is meant to merge two sorted lists into one sorted list, but it drops elements when the lists have different lengths. Find and fix the bug: def merge(a, b):
    out = []
    i = j = 0
    while i < len(a) and j < len(b):
        if a[i] <= b[j]:
            out.append(a[i]); i += 1
        else:
            out.append(b[j]); j += 1
    return out
